It's been long enough since I made the last set of tea towels and the new ones are finally ready and they will be available in my shop this Wednesday! They are featuring 6 of my watercolour patterns: wildflowers chickens, whales, seagulls,cardinals, herons and chicken yoga (not shown in the photos). I made 4 of each design 🌸  I hope you will love them! The fabric is made of organic cotton and it's printed in Poland by @cottonbee_fabrics 💕 And all of them are sewn by myself in my home in Nova Scotia, Canada 🐋🥰 
#teatowels #patterndesign #watercolorpattern

I'm still packing your orders today and they all should be out by the end of the day 📮 It's been a great shop update this time and I didn't expect that as this year has been quite hard businesswise! Not to mention the extremely low posts reach on instagram 🤦🏻‍♀️ So thank you soo much everyone for supporting my hard work 💕 I am really grateful 🙏 I was packing the "Snakebird" print today and I thought I will make some new pictures of it, so here they are 🙂 I think it looks great with this mat (I don't sell it with a mat though!)

For this winter I decided to paint a lot of little penguins 🐧 The original painting is 12" x 16" and this is a second version of the same picture. I didn't like the first one and I painted it all over again. Now I am very happy with the result. I am not sure I will be able to prepare more new winter themes this year but we will see! I also didn't have time to order new fabrics with this design and I really wanted to sew new penguins tea towels 🤷‍♀️ But I guess they will be ready for the next year then. For now I have the original still available, 11" x 14" prints, greeting cards, bookmarks, gift tags and writing sets 😊 Check out my website to see them! This design is also available in the society6 store! Happy Thursday!
